+# Operational Capability Readiness Assessment
+
+**Generated:** 2026-05-24  
+**Assessed by:** Copilot (automated inspection of repository HEAD)  
+**Scope:** Six target operational capabilities against the `Tanjiro-1122/Rune` codebase
+
+---
+
+## How to Read This Document
+
+Each section describes one capability with four sections:
+
+- **Current state** — what exists in the code today
+- **Evidence** — specific file/line citations from the repository
+- **Gaps & blockers** — what is missing or unconnected
+- **Estimated readiness** — a qualitative distance rating
+- **Recommended next steps** — ordered, actionable work items
+
+The ratings in the [capability matrix](#capability-matrix) use this scale:
+
+| Symbol | Meaning |
+|--------|---------|
+| 🟢 **Ready** | Full code path exists, gated, audited; only env vars / approval needed to execute |
+| 🟡 **Partial** | Gate policy and audit exist; executor is present but blocked by a config switch or missing runner |
+| 🟠 **Stub** | Gate policy is registered and auditable; no real executor is wired |
+| 🔴 **Not connected** | No executor exists and the integration is explicitly listed as not wired yet |
+
+---
+
