+---
+
+## 1. Merge
+
+### Current state
+
+A complete, safety-gated merge code path exists and is reachable today.
+
+`lib/privileged-merge.ts` implements `runPrivilegedMerge`, which:
+1. Validates the repo is in the allowlist (`lib/repo-actions.ts` → `isRepoAllowed`).
+2. Fetches the PR via Octokit, collects check-run conclusions, and auto-builds the required evidence (`approved_pr_url`, `passing_checks`, `diff_summary`, `rollback_plan`).
+3. Passes all evidence through `evaluatePrivilegedOperationGate` (`lib/privileged-operations.ts`) which verifies the exact approval phrase `APPROVE RUNE MERGE`, dry-run flag, all required scope and evidence fields.
+4. Writes an audit record to `rune_action_events` via `auditPrivilegedOperationGate`.
+5. On a live (non-dry-run) approved gate, calls `octokit.pulls.merge` with `merge_method: "squash"`.
+
+This is exposed via `POST /api/privileged-operations` with `action: "merge"` (`app/api/privileged-operations/route.ts`).
+
+A second, pipeline-oriented merge path exists in `lib/rune-lifecycle.ts` (`runLifecycle`), used when Rune opens its own PRs and auto-merges them after preview build and security gate checks.
+
+A smoke test asserts the structural invariants in `scripts/privileged-merge-smoke-test.mjs`.
+
+### Evidence
+
+| Artifact | Lines | Notes |
+|---|---|---|
+| `lib/privileged-operations.ts` | 55–66 | `merge` policy: exact phrase, required scope, required evidence, `dryRunRequired: true` |
+| `lib/privileged-merge.ts` | 59–178 | `runPrivilegedMerge` — full gate + Octokit execution |
+| `app/api/privileged-operations/route.ts` | 7–75 | `POST` with `action: "merge"` routes to `runPrivilegedMerge` |
+| `lib/rune-lifecycle.ts` | 190–196, 250–319 | `mergePR` helper and `runLifecycle` pipeline |
+| `supabase/schema.sql` | 262–275 | `rune_action_events` table where all gate audits are persisted |
+| `scripts/privileged-merge-smoke-test.mjs` | 1–13 | Structural assertions on key merge invariants |
+
+### Gaps & blockers
+
+| Gap | Impact |
+|---|---|
+| `GITHUB_TOKEN` or `RUNE_GITHUB_TOKEN` must be set in production | Without it, Octokit client is unauthenticated; private repos and write operations will fail |
+| Target repo must appear in the allowlist (`isRepoAllowed`) | All three managed repos are not automatically allowlisted; this needs confirming per env |
+| `rune_action_events` table schema mismatch (`jarvis_action_events` in old code) may mean historic audit data is on a different table | Audit trail integrity depends on which table name is live in Supabase |
+
+### Estimated readiness
+
+🟢 **Ready** — the full code path is implemented, gated, and audited. Merge can execute today once `GITHUB_TOKEN` is set and the target repo is allowlisted. The dry-run mode allows safe testing before first live execution.
+
+### Recommended next steps
+
+1. Confirm `GITHUB_TOKEN` (or `RUNE_GITHUB_TOKEN`) is set as a Vercel/production env var.
+2. Run a dry-run merge (`dryRun: true`) against a known open PR and confirm the gate result and audit log entry.
+3. Verify `rune_action_events` (not `jarvis_action_events`) is the live table in Supabase.
+4. Test one live squash merge to confirm end-to-end.
+
