+## 3. Rollback
+
+### Current state
+
+Rollback is structurally identical to deploy. `lib/deployment-control.ts` handles `action: "execute_rollback"` in `executeDeploymentControlAction`. The policy is registered with phrase `APPROVE RUNE ROLLBACK`.
+
+The logic:
+1. Lists recent Vercel production deployments.
+2. Finds the most recent `READY` deployment that is not index-0 (i.e., not the current one) as the rollback candidate.
+3. Constructs `vercel rollback <url> --token=$VERCEL_TOKEN`.
+4. Queues or blocks depending on `RUNE_DEPLOYMENT_MUTATION_MODE`.
+
+A simpler `rollbackProduction()` function also exists in `lib/rune-lifecycle.ts`, which calls Vercel v13 API directly to promote the `deployments[1]` deployment.
+
+### Evidence
+
+| Artifact | Lines | Notes |
+|---|---|---|
+| `lib/privileged-operations.ts` | 79–90 | `rollback` policy: phrase `APPROVE RUNE ROLLBACK`, required evidence includes `blast_radius` |
+| `lib/deployment-control.ts` | 125–183 | `prepareDeploymentControlAction` — identifies rollback candidate |
+| `lib/deployment-control.ts` | 197–348 | `executeDeploymentControlAction` — handles `execute_rollback` |
+| `lib/cli-runner-jobs.ts` | 4–6 | `"vercel rollback "` is an allowlisted command prefix |
+| `lib/rune-lifecycle.ts` | 322–349 | `rollbackProduction()` — direct Vercel API rollback |
+| `scripts/privileged-operations-control-plane-smoke-test.mjs` | 4–16 | Asserts `rollback` policy and phrase |
+
+### Gaps & blockers
+
+Same as deploy (runner, `RUNE_DEPLOYMENT_MUTATION_MODE`, `VERCEL_TOKEN`). Additionally:
+
+| Gap | Impact |
+|---|---|
+| Rollback candidate selection is index-based (`deployments[1]`) | If recent deployments include preview builds or failed states, the wrong deployment may be selected; explicit `deploymentId` parameter should be confirmed in practice |
+| No automated smoke test of rollback candidate selection logic | Rollback to wrong version could cause an outage longer than the original issue |
+
+### Estimated readiness
+
+🟡 **Partial** — same status as deploy. All code is in place; the runner process is the only operational blocker.
+
+### Recommended next steps
+
+1. Same as deploy: stand up the CLI runner, set `RUNE_DEPLOYMENT_MUTATION_MODE=cli_runner`.
+2. Run a `prepare_rollback` inspection (`prepareDeploymentControlAction`) against production to confirm the candidate selection returns the intended deployment before any live rollback is approved.
+3. Add a test or assertion on rollback candidate selection logic to guard against off-by-one errors in the deployment list.
+
