+## 4. Change Payments
+
+### Current state
+
+The `change_payments` gate policy is fully registered with the exact approval phrase `APPROVE RUNE PAYMENT CHANGE` and requires evidence fields: `payment_provider`, `affected_products`, `financial_impact`, `reversal_plan`. The `evaluate_gate` action in the privileged-operations API can check completeness and return a gate result with an audit record.
+
+However, **no executor exists**. RevenueCat integration is read-only (`lib/revenuecat-readonly.ts`): it can fetch subscriber info and entitlement status via the RevenueCat REST API (read key), but cannot create prices, cancel subscriptions, issue refunds, or modify any product in Stripe, RevenueCat, or App Store Connect.
+
+`RUNE_NOT_CONNECTED_YET` in `lib/project-registry.ts` explicitly lists:
+> "RevenueCat direct admin/granting controls"
+
+The `RUNE_APPROVAL_REQUIRED_ACTIONS` list includes:
+> "granting credits/free months/subscription changes"
+
+This confirms the current design intent: payment changes are gated and audited but not yet executable.
+
+### Evidence
+
+| Artifact | Lines | Notes |
+|---|---|---|
+| `lib/privileged-operations.ts` | 91–101 | `change_payments` policy: phrase, required evidence, `forbiddenWithoutApproval` list |
+| `lib/revenuecat-readonly.ts` | 1–50 | Read-only subscriber/entitlement lookup; no write methods |
+| `lib/revenuecat-overview.ts` | — | Overview/read-only report; no write methods |
+| `lib/project-registry.ts` | 186–192 | `RUNE_NOT_CONNECTED_YET`: RevenueCat write explicitly listed |
+| `lib/project-registry.ts` | 164–173 | `RUNE_APPROVAL_REQUIRED_ACTIONS` includes subscription changes |
+| `app/api/revenuecat/` | — | API route wraps read-only functions only |
+
+### Gaps & blockers
+
+| Gap | Impact |
+|---|---|
+| No RevenueCat write/admin API client | Cannot grant, revoke, refund, or modify subscriptions; would require the RevenueCat REST API secret key and write endpoints |
+| No Stripe client | Direct Stripe price or product changes are not possible; no client is in the codebase |
+| No App Store Connect in-app purchase management | App Store Connect integration is read-only (build/TestFlight status); IAP changes are not wired |
+| Gate evaluation works but returns `canExecute: false` with no executor | Approval would pass the gate but then have nowhere to go |
+
+### Estimated readiness
+
+🔴 **Not connected** — gate policy and audit infrastructure are ready; the integration with any payment provider write API does not exist. A substantial new integration must be built.
+
+### Recommended next steps
+
+1. Decide which payment provider(s) are in scope (RevenueCat admin API, Stripe, or both).
+2. Obtain and vault a RevenueCat Secret API key (`REVENUECAT_SECRET_KEY`) separate from the existing read key.
+3. Build a `lib/revenuecat-admin.ts` module that wraps the RevenueCat [grant promotional entitlement](https://www.revenuecat.com/reference/grant-a-promotional-entitlement), revoke, and subscriber-update endpoints behind the existing gate.
+4. Wire the executor into the privileged-operations API route as a new `action: "change_payments"` handler.
+5. Write a dry-run smoke test to confirm gate → audit → executor flow end-to-end.
+
